routeFacts.name: Nahverkehr Dresden
routeFacts.description:
Experience complex operations with commuters and international travellers converging to make a hustle and bustle mix of traffic. Be in control of modern traction, and explore the countryside of Train Sim World 2: Rush Hour - Nahverkehr Dresden. Feel the rush with brand new passengers. As you travel from station-to-station you will see a greater variety in passengers and higher passenger volumes at peak times. All recreating the hustle and bustle of Rush Hour.
The line between Dresden and Riesa was one of Germany’s first long-distance railways. Today the line’s importance keeps it busy, fast services beat the regional traffic through the use of separate fast and slow lines, and the outskirts of Dresden are served by frequent commuter services.
routeInfo: This route includes the 55km railway between Dresden Hbf and Riesa Hbf, along with the 23km fast line which runs parallel to the slow line for a portion of the route. In addition, this route also features a 5km branch towards Großenhain Cottbuser Bahnhof and a 9km branch towards Meißen Triebischtal (Meißen branch was added later as a free update). The route is included in the Rush Hour Season Pass.
